Um pilar de luz toma a aparência de estreitas colunas que, por vezes, se estendem verticalmente acima ou abaixo da fonte de luz.

🇬🇧🇺🇸'Pillars of light' captured in Watertown, South Dakota. Pillars of light are an optical phenomenon formed by the reflection of sun or moonlight by ice crystals that are present in Earth's atmosphere. A pillar of light takes the appearance of narrow columns that sometimes extend vertically above or below the light source.
